<paragraph blockId="17.[93,1048,107,195]" box="[93,212,107,131]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">
<emphasis box="[93,212,107,131]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[93,1048,107,195]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nogueira" authorityYear="2001" box="[257,416,139,163]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Grubeosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="breviarticulata">
<emphasis box="[257,416,139,163]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">breviarticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the small size of the blades of the compound chaetae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[93,1049,240,1027]" box="[93,209,240,263]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">
<emphasis box="[93,209,240,263]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">Discussion</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[93,1049,240,1027]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">
The most characteristic features of 
<taxonomicName authority="Nogueira, 2001" authorityName="Nogueira" authorityYear="2001" box="[555,863,270,294]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Grubeosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="breviarticulata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[555,863,270,294]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">Grubeosyllis breviarticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[875,940,271,294]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are long dorsal cirri and short-bladed falcigers. Only few species of this genus share similar characteristics. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hartmann-Schroder" baseAuthorityYear="1960" box="[272,485,334,358]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Grubeosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="balani">
<emphasis box="[272,485,334,358]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">Grubeosyllis balani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hartmann-SchroÈder, 1960) diOEers because: (1) the median antenna is inserted more anteriorly on the prostomium, between the anterior pair of eyes; (2) the dorsal cirri of chaetiger 1 are about the same size as the following cirri and all of them are shorter and have broader bases; and (3) the blades of the compound chaetae have a larger gap between distal and proximal teeth and are even shorter than those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Nogueira, 2001" authorityName="Nogueira" authorityYear="2001" box="[495,690,493,517]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Grubeosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="breviarticulata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[495,690,493,517]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">G. breviarticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[698,760,494,517]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, about 
<quantity box="[850,930,493,517]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" unit="m" value="4.75" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="4.0">
4±5.5 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[916,930,493,517]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">m</emphasis>
</quantity>
m long on anterior parapodia, and 
<quantity box="[369,429,525,549]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" unit="m" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">
3±4 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[415,429,525,549]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">m</emphasis>
</quantity>
m on posterior ones (see 
<bibRefCitation author="ALOAS, C. &amp; SAN MARTIAN, G. &amp; SARDAA, R." box="[708,886,524,549]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" pagination="285" refId="ref11219" refString="ALOAS, C., SAN MARTIAN, G. and SARDAA, R., 1983, Tres nuevos SiAllidos para el litoral ibeArico: Exogone rostrata (Naville, 1933), Parapionosylli s brevicirra (Day, 1954) y Pseudobrania balani (Hartmann-SchroEder, 1960), InvestigacioAn Pesquera, 47 (2), 285 ± 294." type="journal article" year="1983">
AloÂs 
<emphasis box="[766,813,525,549]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">et al</emphasis>
., 1983
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="(Banse, 1972)" baseAuthorityName="Banse" baseAuthorityYear="1972" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Grubeosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="brevipharyngea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">Grubeosyllis brevipharyngea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="BANSE, K." box="[284,423,557,581]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" pagination="191" refId="ref11431" refString="BANSE, K., 1972, On some species of Phyllodocidae, Syllidae, Nephtyidae, Goniadidae, Apistobranchidae, and Spionidae (Polychaeta) from the Northeast Paci ® c Ocean, Paci W c Science, 26 (2), 191 ± 222." type="journal article" year="1972">Banse, 1972</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Nogueira, 2001" authorityName="Nogueira" authorityYear="2001" box="[774,973,557,581]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Grubeosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="breviarticulata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[774,973,557,581]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">G. breviarticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[984,1049,558,581]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
because in this species: (1) the palps are totally fused; (2) the peristomium is not dorsally reduced; (3) the dorsal cirri of chaetiger 1 are similar in length to the following cirri; (4) the acicula are distally blunt; (5) each parapodium has seven to nine compound chaetae; (6) there is a strong gradation in size of the chaetae and only the ventralmost are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Nogueira, 2001" authorityName="Nogueira" authorityYear="2001" box="[605,802,717,741]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Grubeosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="breviarticulata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[605,802,717,741]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">G. breviarticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[810,873,717,740]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; (7) the dorsal simple chaeta is present from the anterior chaetigers; and (8) the pharynx is shorter, extending only through three chaetigers, against four in 
<taxonomicName authority="Nogueira, 2001" authorityName="Nogueira" authorityYear="2001" box="[771,970,781,805]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Grubeosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="breviarticulata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[771,970,781,805]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">G. breviarticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[982,1048,781,804]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Finally, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="San Martin" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[190,416,812,836]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Grubeosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="yraidae">
<emphasis box="[190,416,812,836]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">Grubeosyllis yraidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
San MartõÂn, 1984a is separated from 
<taxonomicName authority="Nogueira, 2001" authorityName="Nogueira" authorityYear="2001" box="[853,1049,812,836]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Grubeosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="breviarticulata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[853,1049,812,836]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788">G. breviarticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[93,155,845,868]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1788" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
because the former species has: (1) the palps almost completely fused; (2) the peristomium not reduced; (3) the acicula with very short tip; (4) the blades of superior falcigers with long spines; (5) the blades of inferior falcigers with the proximal tooth very reduced, resembling a spine; (6) the pharynx shorter, only extending through two or three segments; and (7) the pharyngeal tooth placed away from the anterior margin of the pharynx.
</paragraph>
